CREATED:20260623T080000Z
DESCRIPTION:The Chinese New Year marks the start of the lunar new year, which occurs sometime between Jan. 21 and Feb. 20. Also known as the Spring Festival, it is considered one of China’s most important celebrations, with each year being named after one of the 12 animals in the Chinese zodiac. Festivities include fireworks, parades, and performances. The holiday closes with a lantern festival.\n\nChinese New Year\n\nInformation provided by www.officeholidays.com
URL:https://www.officeholidays.com/holidays/china/chinese-new-year
